com.bigdata.rdf.sparql.ast

Class FunctionRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.rdf.sparql.ast.FunctionRegistry

  • public class FunctionRegistry
extends Object
    Registry for built-in and external SPARQL functions.

    Note: Use an alternative namespace for functions which do not have official namespaces.

    See Also:
    XPath functions, Sparql functions TODO We should restrict registration of functions in the {@link BD#NAMESPACE} to static initialization. The code already does not permit replacement of registered functions.

        public static final void checkArgs(ValueExpressionNode[] args,
             Class... types)
        Verify type constraints.
        Parameters:
        args - The arguments to some function.
        types - The type constraints. If there are more arguments given than constraints, then the last constraint in this vararg parameter will be used to validate the additional arguments.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the type constraints are violated.

      • toVE

        public static final IValueExpression<? extends IV> toVE(BOpContextBase context,
                                  GlobalAnnotations globals,
                                  org.openrdf.model.URI functionURI,
                                  Map<String,Object> scalarValues,
                                  ValueExpressionNode... args)
        Convert a FunctionNode into an IValueExpression.
        Parameters:
        globals - The global annotations, including the lexicon namespace.
        functionURI - The function URI.
        scalarValues - Scalar values for the function (optional). This is used for things like the separator in GROUP_CONCAT.
        args - The function arguments.
        Returns:
        The IValueExpression.
